      "appCustomProperties": {
        "state": "engineered",
        "edbb": {
          "role": "trading",
          "intro": "A maximum-tonnage trade fit that keeps a defensive shield. Initial is the cheapest buy-only hull packed with cargo; A-Rated is the trade baseline with a bi-weave and booster suite; Engineered maximises laden jump range, mobility and survivability. Strip the shield for absolute max cargo on safe routes.",
          "callout": {
            "label": "Cargo first, but keep a shield",
            "text": "The Panther's whole purpose is tonnage — fill the internals with the biggest cargo racks. But unlike a Type-9, it has the slots and utilities to keep a real bi-weave shield and booster suite, so run defended on valuable routes and strip the shield only for safe maximum-cargo hauls."
          },
          "notes": {
            "TinyHardpoint1": "First Heavy-Duty shield booster — the cheapest large multiplier on the bi-weave's modest MJ.",
            "TinyHardpoint2": "Second Heavy-Duty booster stacks more shield to survive interdictions while laden.",
            "TinyHardpoint3": "Optional / low-priority — Ammo Capacity adds rounds. Point Defence shoots down incoming missiles and torpedoes.",
            "TinyHardpoint4": "Optional / low-priority — Ammo Capacity adds heat-sink charges. Dumps heat for silent running and Thermal-Vent resets.",
            "TinyHardpoint5": "Third Heavy-Duty booster rounds out the defensive shield stack.",
            "PowerPlant": "Class-8 A plant; Low Emissions runs it cool and quiet, Thermal Spread bleeds the rest.",
            "MainEngines": "A-rate + Dirty Drives so a 1,200t hull laden still boosts away from danger.",
            "FrameShiftDrive": "A-rate + Increased Range with Mass Manager — laden jump range sets route efficiency.",
            "LifeSupport": "D-rate to save mass; Lightweight trims more, and life support has no experimental effect.",
            "PowerDistributor": "A-rate + Engine Focused with Super Conduits to sustain boost on the heavy hull.",
            "Radar": "Drop to D and go Lightweight; a hauler needs no sensor range, so save the mass.",
            "FuelTank": "Stock C tank; fuel capacity is fixed and cannot be engineered.",
            "Slot01_Size8": "Optional — Expanded Capacity adds cargo space; worth it for dedicated haulers. Holds cargo.",
            "Slot02_Size8": "Optional — Expanded Capacity adds cargo space; worth it for dedicated haulers. Holds cargo.",
